CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 26, 1957, pg. 1, reads: "United for Freedom - Once again, retired baseball star, Jackie Robinson, 1956 Springarn Medal recipient, and the man who brought him into the major leagues, join hands in a worthy endeavor. Both addressed a mass rally Monday night at Wesley Center AME Zion Church, in interest of the NAACP's '1957 Fight for Freedom Fund,' of which Jackie is national chairman.  Here, the 'Top Branch' advises his 'protege' on a deep point. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Man holding film camera in front of baseball player Jackie Robinson and baseball executive Branch Rickey seated on sofa
